            <text>
                <body>
                    <div type="edition">
                        <div type="textpart">
                            <ab>L’<rs key="#Emperor/king">imperatore</rs>
                        <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/267">Ludovico</persName> siede in
                            <rs key="#Assembly">giudizio</rs>, alla destra di <rs key="#Popes"
                            >papa</rs>
                        <persName key="#Popes" ref="#people/266">Benedetto</persName>, <placeName
                            ref="#places/52"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Mention #Residential #Palatium #Laubia/topia #Itinerary #Mother_churches #Popes"
                                ><rs key="#Itinerary">Romam</rs></placeName>, in <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Mention #Residential #Palatium">palacio</rs> quod
                        est fundatum iusta <orgName key="#Mother_churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/201"><rs key="#Mother_churches">basilica</rs>
                            beatissimi Petri principis apostolorum</orgName>, in <rs
                            key="#Laubia/topia">laubia magiore</rs> ipsius palacii; assistono, fra
                        gli altri, <persName key="#Bishops"><name ref="Petrus"
                            >Pietro</name></persName>, <persName key="#Bishops"><name
                                ref="Silvester">Silvestro</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops"><name ref="Ursus">Orso</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops"><name ref="Leo">Leone</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops"><name ref="Romanus">Romano</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops"><name ref="Iohannes">Giovanni</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Bishops"><name ref="Allo">Alone</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Bishops"><name ref="Bonosus">Bonoso</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Bishops"><name ref="Gregorius"
                            >Gregorio</name></persName>, altro <persName key="#Bishops"><name
                                ref="Romanus">Romano</name></persName>, <persName key="#Bishops"
                                ><name ref="Cosmas">Cosma</name></persName>, altro <persName
                            key="#Bishops"><name ref="Gregorius">Gregorio</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopis</rs> uius <rs key="#Areas">Romanie
                        finibus</rs>; i <rs key="#Bishops">vescovi</rs> Odalberto di <placeName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#places/67">Luni</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/78">Adalberto</persName> di <placeName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#places/10">Bergamo</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/20">Everardo</persName> di <placeName
                            ref="#places/43" key="#Bishops">Piacenza</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/269">Garibaldo</persName> di <placeName
                            ref="#places/245" key="#Bishops">Novara</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/138">Elbungo</persName> di <placeName
                            ref="#places/53" key="#Bishops">Parma</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/270">Ildegherio</persName> di <placeName
                            ref="#places/262" key="#Bishops">Lodi</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/216">Ardengo</persName> di <placeName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#places/9">Brescia</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/271">Grasulfo</persName> di <placeName
                            ref="#places/2" key="#Bishops">Firenze</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/272">Alboino</persName> di <placeName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#places/128">Volterra</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/273">Pietro</persName> di <placeName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#places/505">Arezzo</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/274">Erlando</persName> di <placeName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#places/506">Fiesole</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/275">Asterio</persName> di <placeName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#places/507">Pistoia</placeName>; i <rs key="#Count"
                            >conti</rs>
                        <persName key="#Count" ref="#people/278">Adelelmo</persName>, <persName
                            key="#Count" ref="#people/277">Rotbaldo</persName> e <persName
                            key="#Count" ref="#people/276">Gottifridi</persName>; <persName
                            key="#Judge"><name ref="Stefanus">Stefano</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Judge" ref="#people/280">Teofilatto</persName>, <persName
                            key="#Papal_court_officer #Judge"><name ref="Gregorius"
                            >Gregorio</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Papal_court_officer">omiculator</rs>, <persName key="#Judge"><name
                                ref="Gratianus">Graziano</name></persName>, <persName key="#Judge"
                                ><name ref="Hadrianus">Adriano</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Judge"><name ref="Theodorus">Teodoro</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Judge"><name ref="Leo">Leone</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Judge"><name ref="Crescentius">Crescenzio</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Judge"><name ref="Benedictus"
                            >Benedetto</name></persName>, <persName key="#Judge"><name
                                ref="Iohannes">Giovanni</name></persName>, <persName key="#Judge"
                                ><name ref="Anastasius">Anastasio</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudices</rs> huhic Romanie; Walperto, Aquilino, Farimundo,
                            <persName key="#Judge"><name ref="Viventius/Boderadus">Vivenzio detto
                                Boderato</name></persName>, Stabile e Stadelberto <rs key="#Judge"
                            >iudices idem augusti</rs>; <persName key="#Notary"><name ref="Petrus"
                                >Pietro</name></persName>, <persName key="#Notary"><name
                                ref="Sicardus">Sicardo</name></persName> e <persName key="#Notary"
                                ><name ref="Teutelmus">Teutelmo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notai del sacro palazzo</rs>; <persName ref="#people/144"
                            >Winigildo</persName>, <persName><name ref="Audebertus"
                            >Auberto</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Suppo"
                            >Suppone</name></persName> e altro <persName><name ref="Winigildus"
                                >Winigildo</name></persName>. Si presenta <persName
                            ref="#people/213" key="#Bishops">Pietro</persName>, <rs key="#Bishops"
                            >vescovo</rs> di <placeName ref="#places/4"
                            key="#Cities #Mother_churches #Bishops">Lucca</placeName>, con il suo
                            <rs key="#Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities">advocatus</rs>
                        <persName key="#Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities"><name
                                ref="Eleazar/Bonitius">Eliezar detto Bonizio</name></persName> del
                            <persName>fu <name ref="Eriteus">Eriteo</name></persName>, dichiarando
                        che iam plures vices ha denunciato all’imperatore, tamque in <rs
                            key="#Cities">civitate</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/65">Papia</placeName> quamque et per
                        alias locas, <persName ref="#people/147">Lamberto</persName> del <persName
                            ref="#people/268">fu Rodilando</persName> de <rs key="#Cities"
                            >civitate</rs> Lucense, il quale tiene iniuste casas et res che spettano
                            <orgName key="#Mother_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/68"><rs
                                key="#Mother_churches">ecclesie</rs> Lucense</orgName>: infra eadem
                        civitate, l’<rs key="#Slave">ancilla</rs>
                        <persName key="#Slave"><name ref="Adreberga">Adreperga</name></persName>,
                        casis et rebus poste in locas et fundas <placeName ref="#places/357"
                            >Castelioni</placeName> prope <placeName ref="#places/357"
                            >Sudrominio</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/91">Cornino</placeName>
                        hubi dicitur <placeName ref="#places/133">Casale Lapi</placeName>,
                            <placeName ref="#places/508">Monterioni</placeName><geogName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/87"><rs key="#Comitatus">comitato</rs>
                            <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/86"
                            >Popoloniense</placeName></geogName>, un appezzamento di terra posto
                        hubi dicitur <placeName ref="#places/4">a Pulia</placeName>, in loco et
                        fundo <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/509">Camiano</placeName> prope
                            <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio Elsa</rs>, in loco et fundo <placeName
                            ref="#places/239">Quaraciano</placeName> hubi dicitur <placeName
                            ref="#places/510">Miliano</placeName> et <placeName ref="#places/512"
                            >Pluciano</placeName>, in loco et fundo <placeName ref="#places/514"
                            >Miciano</placeName>, res poste in <placeName ref="#places/513"
                            >Conca</placeName>, la <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/266"><rs key="#Churches">chiesa</rs> Sancti
                            Mauricii in loco et fundo <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/511"
                                >Filituli</placeName></orgName>. Avendo l’imperatore inviato
                        all’accusato una <rs key="#Littera/mandatum">epistola ad vestro anolo
                            sigilata</rs>, con l’ordine di recarsi civitate Luca o ihic civitate
                        Roma alla sua presenza, iusticiam faciendum, e non essendosi quest’ultimo
                        presentato, il vescovo chiede di essere investito delle suddette casis et
                        rebus salva querela. L’imperatore ordina a <persName
                            key="#Missus_regis #vassusOf" ref="#people/279">Walteri</persName>, <rs
                            key="#vassusOf">vassus</rs> et <rs key="#Missus_regis">missus</rs> suo,
                        di procedere all’investitura per fuste e pone sopra gli stessi beni un <rs
                            key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">banno imperiale</rs> di <rs
                            key="#Penalty">2000 mancusi d’oro</rs>; metà da versare alla <rs
                            key="#Camera_regis">camera imperiale</rs>, metà pars del vescovato.
                        L’inviato e i giudici imperiali chiedono al <rs key="#Writer #Notary">notaio
                            imperiale</rs>
                        <persName key="#Writer #Notary"><name ref="Thomas">Tommaso</name></persName>
                        la scrittura della noticia. <rs key="#Witness">Testimoni</rs>
                        sottoscrittori: <persName key="#Witness #Bishops" ref="#people/139"
                            >Odalberto</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs>, <persName key="#Witness #Judge"><name
                                ref="Walpertus">Walperto</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudex domni imperatoris</rs>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Aquilinus">Aquilino</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudex domni imperatoris</rs>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Farimundus">Farimundo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudex domni imperatoris</rs>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Stabilis">Stabile</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudex domni imperatoris</rs>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Stadelbertus"
                            >Stadelberto</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudex domni imperatoris</rs>.</ab>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                        <p>MDL, 5/3, n. 1768, pp. 639-640; DD L III, n. 6, pp. 18-21; Manaresi, n.
                    111, pp. 410-414;
                    <ref>http://saame.it/fonte/placiti-toscani-toscana-22/</ref>.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div type="bibliography" subtype="additional">
                        <p/>
                    </div>
                    <div type="bibliography" subtype="links">
                        <p/>
                    </div>
                    <div type="commentary">
                        <p>Sottoscrizioni autografe: il vescovo Odalberto, il giudice Walperto, il
                    giudice Aquilino, il giudice Farimundo, il giudice Stabile, il giudice
                    Stadelberto.</p>
                    </div>
                </body>
